 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "UNSOUNDNESS-LEDGER-3: LIVE view ignores bare retractions — silent stale data. Both from_datoms() (store.rs:1052) and apply_datoms() (store.rs:1124) guard LIVE view updates with 'if d.op == Op::Assert'. A Retract datom is inserted into the BTreeSet and all secondary indexes, but the live_view BTreeMap<(EntityId, Attribute), (Value, TxId)> is NEVER updated for retractions. Consequence: if entity E has attribute A asserted with value V1 at tx T1, live_view[(E,A)] = (V1, T1). If a later tx T2 retracts (E, A, V1), live_view STILL shows (V1, T1). The retracted value remains visible to all live_view consumers. This is safe ONLY because the braid protocol uses retract-then-assert (ADR-COHERENCE-001) — every retraction is paired with a new assertion in the same transaction. But the invariant is NOWHERE ENFORCED. If any code path issues a bare retraction without a paired assert (e.g., task deletion, observation cleanup, external merge), the LIVE view silently shows a ghost value. No grep for 'Retract.*live_view' finds any handling. No test covers 'retract without re-assert on live_view'. The fix is a debug_assert in apply_datoms that flags bare retractions, turning a silent-corruption path into a loud one."
